# Better Auth

Auth is configured in `src/lib/server/auth.ts` and wired in `src/hooks.server.ts`.

## Server setup

```ts
import { betterAuth } from 'better-auth/minimal';
import { drizzleAdapter } from 'better-auth/adapters/drizzle';
import { sveltekitCookies } from 'better-auth/svelte-kit';
import { getRequestEvent } from '$app/server';

export const auth = betterAuth({
	appName: PUBLIC_APP_NAME,
	baseURL: ORIGIN,
	secret: BETTER_AUTH_SECRET,
	database: drizzleAdapter(db, { provider: 'pg' }),
	plugins: [
		twoFactor({ issuer: PUBLIC_APP_NAME }),
		sveltekitCookies(getRequestEvent) // must be last
	]
});
```

## Mandatory 2FA (admin only)

- `twoFactor` plugin — TOTP + backup codes; `user.twoFactorEnabled` on session user
- Client: `twoFactorClient` in `src/lib/auth-client.ts` with `onTwoFactorRedirect` → `/login/two-factor`
- Enrollment: `/admin/security/2fa` — set password (GitHub-only), scan QR, verify, save backup codes
- Sign-in challenge: `/login/two-factor` after email or GitHub login when 2FA is enabled
- `admin/+layout.server.ts` redirects to enrollment until `twoFactorEnabled`
- OAuth 2FA gate: `src/lib/server/two-factor-oauth.ts` `after` hook on `/callback/*` (Better Auth only gates email sign-in by default)
- Block `/two-factor/disable` in `hooks.before` — 2FA cannot be turned off

## Hooks

```ts
import { svelteKitHandler } from 'better-auth/svelte-kit';

const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: event.request.headers });
if (session) {
	event.locals.user = session.user;
	event.locals.session = session.session;
}
return svelteKitHandler({ event, resolve, auth, building });
```

## Invite-only admin access

- `admin` plugin — `user.role` (`admin` / `user`); `requireAdmin()` in `$lib/server/auth-guards.ts`
- Bootstrap: empty `user` table → first signup gets `role: 'admin'`
- After bootstrap: `databaseHooks.user.create.before` allows signup only with valid pending invitation (email match or `invite_token` cookie)
- Invitations: `admin_invitation` table + `/admin/users` UI; email via Gmail SMTP (`SMTP_USER`, `SMTP_PASS`) or copy-link fallback
- Accept invite: `/invite/[token]` — email signup or GitHub with `requestSignUp`
- `session.create.before` rejects non-admin sessions
- Check `hasAdmin()`, `isBootstrap()`, `isAdminUser()` from `$lib/server/users`

## Single admin bootstrap (login UI)

- GitHub OAuth is the primary sign-in method
- `emailAndPassword` enabled for bootstrap and invite acceptance
- `disableImplicitSignUp: true` on GitHub provider
- **Bootstrap (`isBootstrap()`):** `/admin/login` shows **Create admin with GitHub** or **Create admin with email** (one time only)
- **After bootstrap:** `/admin/login` is admin sign-in only; `/login` is user sign-in only

## Forms and actions

- Use `auth.api.signInSocial` with `requestSignUp` when bootstrapping admin
- Catch `APIError` from `better-auth/api` and return `fail(400, { message })`
- Protect routes in `load` via `event.locals.user` + `redirect(302, '/login')`
- Types: `User`, `Session` from `better-auth` in `app.d.ts` `Locals`
